message.content:
cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.ME, cs.LG, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with system identification of flexible objects during interaction with a manipulating arm. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper presents an optimal control approach using variational integrators for identifying closed loops in the system. 
- cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering) is relevant as the paper models the object's structure and flexibility by a chain of rigid bodies connected by torsional springs. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is possible as the paper develops a novel method for fast discrete-time adjoint-based gradient calculation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses data recorded from a 7-DOF series elastic robot arm.
